      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKE ROSS NZ (5) has the hoof on the till after placing in handy line-ups on country tracks in his last three outings, last time chasing home NSW Derby winner Hollywood Strip when third in the Wagga Cup. Race fit and looks well placed so can break through. JILLIBY FABIO (8) came from the back row and chased a handy one when placed at Penrith last start. Missed by just a nose over this distance the last time he raced here last month. VINKE B NZ (3) could be working towards a win having finished runner-up in two of his last three starts here, both from wider draws than this. ULTIMATE BIRD NZ (7) is on a quick back-up after adding to a handy record at this circuit and distance with a second on Tuesday. Go well again. TITIAN RAIDER (2) is up in grade but should be peaking after placing in his last two starts and draws well.",
